The paper discusses topic evolution modeling, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of word modeling algorithms and community detection mechanisms suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (cs.SI, cs.DL). The evaluation methods used in the paper, such as pairwise mutual information score and execution time analysis, suggest a focus on data analysis and machine learning (cs.LG).
